Another, equivalent way of discussing supersymmetry breaking is by
examining the supersymmetry
transformations of fermions .
The condition for (at least one) unbroken supersymmetry can
be succinctly summarized as the requirement that  be a pure  [or
] form. Is this condition  satisfied in a vacuum
described by Eqs.  or ? It is easy to see
that Eq.  is equivalent to the condition that  be
"imaginary anti-self
